Since the only vertical asymptote is $x = -2,$ $q(x) = (x + 2)^2.$  Since the horizontal asymptote is $y = 2,$ $\lim_{x \to \infty} p(x)/q(x) = 2,$ which means the leading term of $p(x)$ is $2(x + 2)^2.$  (We could also have $p(x) = -2(x + 2)^2.$)

